sac.game

Class RefutationTableImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • sac.game.RefutationTableImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RefutationTable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RefutationTableAsHashMap, RefutationTableAsTreeMap

    public abstract class RefutationTableImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements RefutationTable
    Abstract initial implementation of transposition table. Meant to be extended by actual implementations of transposition table.
    Author:
    Przemysław Klęsk (wi.zut.edu.pl), Marcin Korzeń (wi.zut.edu.pl)

      • reorder

        public void reorder(GameState parent,
           java.util.List<GameState> children)
        Description copied from interface: RefutationTable
        Reorders the given list of children (for given parent) using information kept in refutation table. More precisely, this method is supposed to put in front the state that caused a cut-off in the previous search iteration. The counter of uses should be updated within this method call.
        Specified by:
        reorder in interface RefutationTable
        Parameters:
        parent - reference to parent state
        children - list of references to children states
